GateDocument.TextWithNodes: IDS 2000 - CALL FOR PAPERS The 10 th International Database Symposium on Mobile , XML and Post-relational Databases as part of The 1 st International Conference on Web Information Systems Engineering ( WISE 2000 ) On June 21 - 22 at Kowloon Shangri- La hotel , Hong Kong organised by ACM Hong Kong Chapter IEEE Hong Kong ( Computer Society ) City University of Hong Kong sponsored by Automated Systems ( Hong Kong ) Limited Informix Software ( China ) Limited Oracle System Hong Kong Limited Sybase Hong Kong Limited BACKGROUND The first International Database Workshop was held in Hong Kong in December 1989 , organized by the Hong Kong Computer Society in corporation with Hong Kong Polytechnic . Its main objective was to promote database technologies in Hong Kong . Its scope was broad coverage of database advanced technologies , methodologies and software tools . The workshop has been an international annual event ever since . The 10 th International Database Symposium will be hosted by the Computer Science Department at City University of Hong Kong . Program suggestions and inquiries should be sent to the conference chairman : Dr Joseph Fong of the City University of Hong Kong , Tat Chee Avenue , Hong Kong , email : csjfong @ xom . hty . rwfvj SCOPE First generation database is hierarchical and network databases . Second generation database is relational database . As the computer technology moves into multimedia and Internet systems , many feel the limitation of relational database in these data intensive application systems . This symposium will discuss the potential candidate for the third generation post-relational database . The XML Wave is coming because it provides a simple , standard , self-describing way of storing and exchanging text and data . A XML-based DBMS provides storage and retrieval of self-describing XML information without having to detour over other formats . We will explore the potential of XML database in the symposium . The combination of business needs to access critical data regardless of location and of opportunities of new personal information services and applications has necessitated mobile database to access data by mobile . The symposium will investigate the computing and data models for mobile system , data management and mobility management for wireless network and the mobile web access and Internet applications . The question for the symposium is whether XML database , mobile database , object-oriented database , multimedia database or Internet Web-based database will be the pote ! ntial post-relational database . PAPER SUBMISSIONS Manuscripts should include an abstract and be limited to 5000 words . Authors should indicate whether their papers are intended for industrial or research sessions . To speed up the review process , authors are encouraged to submit their papers , panel and tutorial proposals electronically according to the submission methods to be announced in the conference web page : http : / / www . cs . cityu . edu . hk / ~ ids 2000 or http : / / www . cs . cityu . edu . hk / ~ wise 2000 .
